---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import Nav from '../../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Crontinel vs Healthchecks.io: Laravel Queue & Cron Monitoring"
  description="Healthchecks.io is a great dead-man switch. But it can't see your queue depth, Horizon state, or job failure rate. Crontinel can."
>
  <Nav />

  <main class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-16">

    <div class="text-center mb-14">
      <div class="inline-block text-xs font-semibold text-gray-400 bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 px-3 py-1 rounded-full mb-4">
        Crontinel vs Healthchecks.io
      </div>
      <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-4">
        Healthchecks.io knows your job ran.<br class="hidden sm:block" /> Crontinel knows <em class="text-green-400 not-italic">why</em> it matters.
      </h1>
      <p class="text-gray-400 max-w-xl mx-auto">
        Healthchecks.io is an excellent open-source dead-man switch: simple, reliable, and free to self-host. But it has no concept of queue depth, Horizon state, or Laravel's scheduler. Crontinel is purpose-built for Laravel.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-8 mb-16">

      <div class="bg-gray-900 border border-gray-800 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-2">What Healthchecks.io does well</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-400">
          You add a ping URL to a cron job. If it doesn't ping within the expected window, you get an alert. It's minimal, open source, and gets the job done for simple heartbeat monitoring. We respect it.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-900 border border-gray-800 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-2">What it can't do for Laravel apps</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-400 mb-4">
          Healthchecks.io knows nothing about what happens inside your app. If Horizon is overwhelmed, a queue is backed up, or a supervisor silently stopped processing; it sees silence without context.
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-400">
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-red-400">✗</span> Can't see Horizon supervisor state</li>
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-red-400">✗</span> Can't measure queue depth or oldest pending job</li>
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-red-400">✗</span> Requires you to wrap every cron job with a curl command</li>
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-red-400">✗</span> No duration or exit code history</li>
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-red-400">✗</span> Alerts after the grace period, not proactively</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

    </div>

    <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-16">
      <table class="w-full text-sm">
        <thead>
          <tr class="border-b border-gray-800 text-left">
            <th class="pb-3 text-gray-400 font-medium">Capability</th>
            <th class="pb-3 text-gray-400 font-medium text-center">Crontinel</th>
            <th class="pb-3 text-gray-400 font-medium text-center">Healthchecks.io</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-800/50">
          {[
            ['Laravel-native (no curl wrapping)', true, false],
            ['Horizon supervisor + paused detection', true, false],
            ['Queue depth + oldest job age', true, false],
            ['Run history with exit codes + duration', true, false],
            ['Dead-man ping monitoring', false, true],
            ['Self-hostable / open source', true, true],
            ['Slack alerts', true, true],
            ['Email alerts', true, true],
            ['Free tier', true, true],
          ].map(([cap, ours, theirs]) => (
            <tr>
              <td class="py-3 text-gray-300">{cap}</td>
              <td class="py-3 text-center">{ours ? <span class="text-green-400">✓</span> : <span class="text-red-400">✗</span>}</td>
              <td class="py-3 text-center">{theirs ? <span class="text-green-400">✓</span> : <span class="text-red-400">✗</span>}</td>
            </tr>
          ))}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-gray-900 border border-green-500/20 rounded-xl p-8 text-center">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-2">Start monitoring the right things</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-400 mb-6">
        Two commands and Crontinel starts tracking every scheduled job automatically.
      </p>
      <div class="bg-gray-950 rounded-lg p-4 font-mono text-sm text-green-400 text-left max-w-sm mx-auto mb-6">
        <div>composer require harunrrayhan/crontinel</div>
        <div>php artisan crontinel:install</div>
      </div>
      <a
        href="/#waitlist"
        class="inline-block bg-green-500 hover:bg-green-400 text-black font-semibold px-6 py-2.5 rounded transition-colors"
      >
        Start free
      </a>
    </div>

  </main>

  <Footer />
</Base>
